He joined Slipknot in January 1999, replacing their original guitarist, Josh Brainard, who left the band during the recording of their self-titled album, reportedly after having fulfilled his recording duties.

Although filling in the spot of rhythm guitar in 1999, Root is considered to be one of the band's main songwriters and has written lead guitar parts for Slipknot's later albums particularly on All Hope is Gone and .5: The Gray Chapter.
Of Slipknot's nine member lineup which lasted between 1999 to 2010, Root was the last to join the band.
On May 17, 2014, Stone Sour released an official statement saying that Root was no longer a member of the band.
